pull.title: Remove unused variable in SortForBlock
pull.body: Although txiter is passed to BlockAssembler::SortForBlock, it is never used. Other than BlockAssembler::addPackageTxs, no other method ever makes a call to SortForBlock, thus making this change harmless.

events.body: Obvious ACK bb079a0. Have you checked if it was ever used and if so what PR changed that?

utACK bb079a0e2c20beb22456c91ad9e11beeae7cdc34.

@sdaftuar Do you know if there was any reason to pass this variable down for a future purpose?
It was unused in c82a4e9a63a, the commit that introduced the code.
Right, IMO should be removed now and added again only when needed.
utACK.  I think this was just an oversight (perhaps leftover from my first implementation which didn't take advantage of ancestor-count-sorting to do the sort).
